ractice educators, students and academics offers hope. This collection of innovative approaches to social work placements addresses subjects including sustainability, student-led services, overseas placements, the value of the third-sector, supporting students from minority groups and the visual arts. The international and diverse contributions offer practical guidance and challenge conventional approaches to placement finding, teaching and assessment in field education. Written from a global social work perspective this is essential reading for anyone responsible for ensuring quality placements for future professionals.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 27. Jan 2023) 0aSocial servicexPractice. 0aSocial workersxTraining of. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Social Work.2bisacsh1 aAdamson, Carole, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAllison, Sallie, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAppleton, Cherie, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBellinger, Avril, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBellinger, Avril, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aBlomfield, Geraldine, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBrown, Peter, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aClarke, Dawn, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCook, Michael, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDoel, Mark, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFord, Deirdre, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFord, Deirdre, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aHazel, Kate, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHigg